value.title: Top two pro-Trump super PACs make final $20 million ad push
value.excerpt: The two leading super PACs that are supporting President Trump's re-election bid are teaming up to shell out $20 million to run ads on TV and digital in seven crucial general election battleground in the closing stretch leading up to Election Day on Tuesday.

value.title: Facebook manually limited New York Post Hunter Biden story: Report
value.excerpt: Facebook fact-checkers manually flagged and restricted distribution of the New York Post's Hunter Biden story, documents obtained by The Guardian show.

value.title: Scott Walker claims Trump has 'fighting chance' in Wisconsin, touts Favre endorsement of president
value.excerpt: President Trump has a "fighting chance" to pull off a surprise victory in Wisconsin, repeating his feat of four years ago, former Republican Gov. Scott Walker told "Your World" Friday.

value.title: Pence returns to Arizona for final push to flip liberal-leaning cities
value.excerpt: In an effort to pick up voters from more progressive counties that voted against the president in 2016, Vice President Mike Pence is returning to the key battleground state of Arizona on Friday.

value.title: Trump rips absentee ballot extensions, says election 'should end on November 3rd'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Friday panned decisions made by some courts that are allowing mail-in or absentee ballots to be counted if they are received by election authorities after Nov. 3, calling the rulings "CRAZY and so bad for our Country."

value.title: John James slams Michigan Senate opponent, says Dems 'freaking out' as Biden, Obama storm state
value.excerpt: Michigan Senate candidate John James reacts on 'Fox & Friends' to Joe Biden and former President Barack Obama campaigning in his state.

value.title: Candace Owens on Lil Wayne's Trump support: Liberals laughed at idea of 'Black Exit' by Dems
value.excerpt: Black Americans leaving the Democratic Party shows they have done nothing for the Black community, according to author Candace Owens on Friday.

value.title: Lil Wayne reveals 'great meeting' with Trump, prompting Twitter users to respond
value.excerpt: Lil Wayne made a big splash on Twitter after he revealed that he met with Trump, sharing a friendly photo the two of them took together.

value.title: Sean Hannity: Biden depicting ‘scary’ image of America despite surging economy
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is making America out to be a country besieged by doom and gloom with five days left until the election, but “Hannity” host Sean Hannity argued Thursday the nation is actually on an upswing.

value.title: Trump meets with Army unit that conducted Al-Baghdadi raid, awards citation
value.excerpt: President Trump has awarded a citation to the Army special operations unit that conducted the 2019 raid resulting in the death of notorious Islamic State leader Abu Bakr Al-Baghdadi.

value.title: Retired Minnesota police officers asked to be Trump poll watchers in 'rough neighborhoods'
value.excerpt: A volunteer attorney for the Trump 2020 campaign is seeking retired officers to work as poll challengers in Minnesota.

value.title: Former Michigan Gov. Rick Snyder on being a 'proud Republican' who voted for Biden
value.excerpt: Snyder served eight years as governor and was replaced by Democrat Gretchen Whitmer in 2019.

value.title: Pence stumps for vulnerable GOP senators resisting Democrat takeover
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is campaigning with four GOP senators this week in an effort to boost their precarious standing in races that will help determine which party controls the upper chamber of Congress.

value.title: Pelosi: 'I feel very confident that Joe Biden will be elected president on Tuesday'
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi projected Thursday that Joe Biden would win the White House and said Democrats are ready to work with him on a transition agenda to tackle the coronavirus pandemic, address the economic fallout and pass an infrastructure agenda.

value.title: 'Media silence' on Hunter Biden allegations is 'hypocritical, concerning to American people': Ronna McDaniel
value.excerpt: The “media silence” around 2020 Democratic presidential hopeful Joe Biden's suspicious ties with foreign businesses has been “hypocritical” and “concerning to the American people,” Republican National Committee Chairwoman Ronna McDaniel said Thursday.

value.title: Biden dismisses record economic growth as not 'nearly enough' to dig out of 'deep' recession
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden dismissed the U.S. economy's record-shattering growth as not "nearly enough" to get the country out of a "deep hole" on Thursday.

value.title: Former Democrat Rubin on why he is voting for Trump: 'No feeling of patriotism' on the left anymore
value.excerpt: President Trump is the last bastion to stopping the radical left, talk show host Dave Rubin said Thursday.

value.title: Joe Biden is a 'Trojan Horse' for socialism, says Tammy Bruce
value.excerpt: 2020 Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden is being used as a "trojan horse," Fox News contributor Tammy Bruce said on Thursday.

value.title: Vote for Joe Biden? Seriously?
value.excerpt: Biden is Bernie Sanders’s grim party in sheep's clothing.

value.title: Trump Jr. warns election is 'about freedom versus tyranny, capitalism versus socialism and Communism'
value.excerpt: The Democrats' "endgame" is to transform America into a far-left, Marxist state where dissent is not permitted, Donald Trump Jr. told "Hannity" Wednesday night.

value.title: Colorado AG steps in after landlord allegedly threatens rent raise at mobile home park if Biden wins
value.excerpt: Colorado’s Attorney General sent a cease and desist letter to the owner of a mobile home park in Fort Morgan, Colo., following reports of voter intimidation after the landlord allegedly threatened to spike rent rates should Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden win on Nov. 3.

value.title: FBI reveals alleged Whitmer kidnapper plotter also wanted to hang Trump, disproving Democrats' narrative
value.excerpt: Some Democrats have blamed the president's inflammatory rhetoric with inciting the kidnap scheme.

value.title: Buttigieg defends Biden, claims Dems 'would have chosen somebody else' if they wanted fracking ban
value.excerpt: "The Story" host Martha MacCallum pressed Joe Biden campaign surrogate Pete Buttigieg Wednesday over the 2020 Democratic nominee's position on fracking and the oil industry following repeated attempts to clarify earlier comments on the issue.

value.title: AOC appears in Vanity Fair in outfits worth $14,000 to curse Trump out
value.excerpt: Freshman Democratic congresswoman Alexandria Ocasio Cortez wore thousands of dollars worth of outfits and jewelry for her spread in Vanity Fair magazine's December issue while attacking President Trump for not paying his taxes.

value.title: Man arrested at Trump rally in Maine carrying knife and wooden baton
value.excerpt: A man wielding a knife and wooden baton was arrested at a campaign rally for President Trump in Maine Wednesday where Gov. Kristi Noem appeared.

value.title: Trump administration moves to change H-1B guest worker program to prioritize higher-wage applicants
value.excerpt: The Department of Homeland Security moved to make a significant change to the controversial guest worker program that would prioritize higher-paid applicants.

value.title: White House’s Stephen Miller warns of ‘nationwide catch and release’ if Biden is elected
value.excerpt: White House adviser Stephen Miller on Wednesday warned of a policy of “nationwide catch and release” if Democratic nominee Joe Biden is elected to the White House -- painting a stark contrast with the Trump administration’s stance on immigration.

value.title: Philadelphia DA threatens Trump over president's call for poll watchers: 'I've got something for you'
value.excerpt: Philadelphia’s district attorney on Wednesday threatened President Donald Trump if he sent “uncertified” poll watchers to the city, telling him in a statement, “I’ve got something for you” if any attempts are made to interfere with Election Day activities.

value.title: Ben Shapiro calls Biden a 'gateway drug to radicalism', not a return to normalcy
value.excerpt: Joe Biden has based his presidential campaign on a promise to restore "normalcy" if he unseats President Trump, but the former vice president will act as nothing more than "a gateway drug to radicalism,

value.title: Ari Fleischer: Biden is 'taking advantage of' a 'broken-down media' that is 'biased against Trump'
value.excerpt: The Biden campaign is "taking advantage" of the media bias against President Trump to keep the controversy surrounding former Vice President Joe Biden's son Hunter out of the spotlight, former White House Press Secretary Ari Fleischer claimed Wednesday.
